Uni-task OR ONE TASK

We have often done a lot of multitasking, but at some point of time the tasks overburden and we end up doing nothing!

I teamed up with a developer to create an App that would help users focus on single task at hand and move a lot of tasks to closure!

Initial Brainstorming and market research:

Even while creating this portfolio - there are various aspects to take care of, different pages to create and I would unknowingly spend a lot of time in a very irrelevant task. This is where the App helped!

We looked for similar apps in the iOS and Android Market. There was nothing which was simple and straight forward.

User Research:

I discussed with few multi-taskers and could see that in the end they were practising mindfulness and doing one task at a time.

 

In conclusion there were 2 different and distinct Personas and everyone needed Uni-task :)

 

 

  • "Too many things to do in a day is overwhelming. I want to make a list of all my tasks and generate a random task individually so that I can focus only on that task!"

    Linda: Persona for someone who has a lot of small independent tasks!

    LINDA

  • "I'd rather break my huge task into smaller independent tasks and complete each of them in small chunks."

    John: Persona for someone who has a huge task at hand and wants to split it and do one at a time.

    JOHN

THE FINAL APP

  • I created the screens just by Using MS Word during the brainstorming and we just stuck to it!

  • The prototype was developed using InVision. 

  • This simple App and Webpage was developed using only 4 screens. MINIMAL and SIMPLE

  • The logo is a simple 1 in a box

LESSONS LEARNT:

This journey taught me the essential aspects of designing in a small time frame, using existing tools.

 

I was able to understand how to keep in mind, even if it is a simple app, the UX plays a major role.
